The article discusses a presidential memorandum issued by President Donald Trump on August 18, 2017. The memorandum states that U.S. Cyber Command will be elevated to a Unified Combatant Command. The Secretary of Defense is directed to recommend an officer for nomination and Senate confirmation as commander of U.S. Cyber Command. The memorandum assigns U.S. Cyber Command various responsibilities, including those previously assigned to the Commander of U.S. Strategic Command. The Secretary of Defense, in coordination with the Director of National Intelligence, is also instructed to provide a recommendation and plan regarding the command relationship between U.S. Cyber Command and the National Security Agency. The memorandum concludes by directing Congress to be notified and authorizes the publication of the memorandum in the Federal Register.